section.t:
Thos updates are sent via UDP multicast and repesent updates of a filelist of a client. A client SHOULD NOT sent updates of offered files, instead of offering his file list to other clients. One UDP datagram contains exactly one file update, which is the same as one file entry of the file list (with all it's limitations):
hash|TTL|length|virtual path|meta-info\
